    "name": "The Wild Century",
    "profile": "Psych/stoner band from The Netherlands.\r\nJust as mysterious as this reverie arises, it continues to resonate to the depths of your visions. In a sitar-tuned cosmic dimension, harmonic basses and mantric rhythms pump, while the astrals project their ethereal grooves onto everyone's lucidity. The succession of repetitive sounds makes the sound waves almost visually perceptible. The view becomes hazy, the body harmonizes with the tantric melodies, the consciousness fades. Welcome to our trip. This is The Wild Century ! Nowadays a five piece unit with Stan Aarts: vocals / guitars, Joris Verbogt: bass, Butsenzeller: drums, Paola Pica: Hammond organ, Gerton Govers: acoustic guitar/electric sitar. With two album 'Raga Blue' and 'Raw' in their pocket and the third album '5' on it's way !\r\n\r\n​Bookings and info: \r\n\r\nhttp://www.thehuman.be/the-wild-century",
